%%TITLE: SparseSync: Gradient Sparsification with Error Feedback for Distributed Training
%%AUTHORS: Elena Rossi; Jun Park; Fatima Nasser
%%VENUE: Conference on Machine Learning Systems
%%YEAR: 2025
%%TOPIC: distributed training and communication-efficient optimization
%%ABSTRACT_START
SparseSync studies communication-efficient distributed training by combining top-k gradient sparsification with error feedback. The method reduces inter-worker bandwidth while preserving convergence on large mini-batch workloads through accumulated residual correction.
%%ABSTRACT_END
1 Background
Synchronous data-parallel training is often bottlenecked by gradient exchange across workers. We study sparsification schedules that transmit only the most significant coordinates each step.
2 Evaluation
Models are trained on standard image and language benchmarks with deterministic seeds, and we report wall-clock speedups alongside final accuracy under varying compression ratios.
